comments: Hartenstein (NYK) rests his hand on Davis' (LAL) upper arm.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Barrett's (NYK) layup attempt at the basket.
Barrett (NYK) legally contests Russell's (LAL) perimeter shot attempt.
Hartenstein (NYK) grasps and promptly releases Davis' (LAL) jersey as the ball comes off of the rim. The contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Quickley (NYK) engages with Schroder (LAL) and then marginal contact occurs when Quickley releases away from the defender.
After applying defensive pressure on Quickley (NYK), Schroder (LAL) disengages and stumbles into the ball handler, making incidental contact with Randle (NYK).
Hartenstein (NYK) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Schroder (LAL) legally contests Quickley's (NYK) perimeter shot attempt.
Hartenstein (NYK) pursues the loose ball and makes brief contact with Reaves (LAL) after the ball sails over his outstretched hands.
Quickley (NYK) rests his hand on Russell's (LAL) side during the drive and the contact is marginal.
Russell (LAL) lowers his off-arm down during the drive and marginal contact occurs with Quickley (NYK).
Randle (NYK) turns his body slightly and marginal contact occurs with Russell (LAL) after the release of the driving shot attempt.
Russell (LAL) avoids making arm contact with Randle (NYK) and he brushes the ball during Randle's dribble into the frontcourt.
Randle (NYK) holds his off-arm out during his drive into the frontcourt and marginal contact occurs with Russell (LAL).
Schroder (LAL) lunges for the ball and avoids making contact with Randle (NYK) during his dribble.
Hartenstein (NYK) establishes himself in Reaves' (LAL) path and marginal contact occurs as Hartenstein releases away to roll.
Davis (LAL) extends his hand out and makes contact with the ball, which dislodges it from Barrett (NYK). The arm contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
Reaves (LAL) moves alongside Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Reaves (LAL) legally contests Barrett's (NYK) perimeter shot attempt.
Schroder (LAL) and Hart (NYK) come together at the same spot on the floor and marginal contact occurs during the rebounding opportunity.
Hart (NYK) initiates contact with Davis' (LAL) arm that causes him to lose control of the loose ball.
The loose ball does not come down out of bounds and play should have continued on.
Hart (NYK) and Russell (LAL) engage disengage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.
Davis (LAL) establishes himself in Hart's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the pick.
Hartenstein (NYK) legally contests Davis' (LAL) lob dunk attempt at the basket.
Schroder (LAL) leans in to make a play on the ball and marginal contact occurs with Quickley's (NYK) shoulder.
Schroder (LAL) reaches in for the ball and delivers body contact to Quickley (NYK), which affects his SQBR.
Hartenstein (NYK) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Reaves (LAL) moves alongside Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Quickley (NYK) avoids making contact with Schroder (LAL) during his contest of the driving shot attempt.
Davis (LAL) brings his hand toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Quickley (LAL) that he is able to play on through.
Davis (LAL) commits a take foul on Hart (NYK).
Davis (LAL) firms up on his left leg and marginal contact occurs with Hart (NYK) as he moves around the screen.
Russell (LAL) and Hart (NYK) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Hart (NYK) legally contests Russell's (LAL) perimeter shot attempt.
Quickley (NYK) and Beasley (LAL) engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
